This paper is primarily focused on video segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of reinforcement learning to improve the segmentation process suggests that it may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the application of this technique to face videos may also make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the use of real-time processing speed may suggest that it could also be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) category.
